node.text: For the first time in over a decade, @SoliBailey found himself land-locked at home in Australia. He made the most of his time and scored ridiculously good waves in his own backyard. From small beachies to heavy slabs, Soli can do it all with power and style. "I want these edits to showcase how much of an all-around surfer Soli Bailey is and why he is one of Australia’s best. From big airs to his powerful rail game and a knack for reading tubes of consequence, these edits will be high in action with minimal fluff. The goal is to get you psyched to go surfing and hit the road in your own backyard wherever that may be." - @MallMic

node.title: Vantage Points: Soli Bailey & Mikey Mallalieu

node.text:
After spending around five years tracking it down, @JordySmith88 has reunited with his first-ever surfboard shaped by his father, @GrahamSmithSurfboards. The 4'6" board was inspired by the era of ...Lost videos when Jordy was digging the round nose shapes with front grips. An exciting moment in Jordy's life to retrieve this board, which he is now hoping to pass down to his newborn son.

Sending a big congratulations to the new parents, @JordySmith88 and @Lyndall_M_Smith, on the birth of their son, Ziggy Smith.

node.text:
Florida icon and full-time family man @CoryLopez hits the road with his two kids, @alana_lopez11 and @lukethedudelopez, on a mission to reap the rewards of a classic Gulf Coast hurricane swell. It’s rad to see how Cory has passed the stoke on to his two groms as they have some fun and paddle into a few fun waves. After manning the Jet Ski, Lopey still manages to lay it down and put on a clinic in any lineup, showing that “The O’Neill Kids Are Alright” in this crazy world. 📹: @christianoehmke
